# Cursor Rules for Node.js Learning Project

## Project Structure
- Use Express.js for routing
- Keep database logic in config/database.js
- Controllers handle business logic
- Routes define endpoints
- Models go in models/ folder
- Utils contain reusable functions
- This project is running in windows machine 
- you must write a industry standard.

## Code Style
- Use ES6+ syntax
- Follow RESTful API conventions
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Error handling should be in try-catch blocks

## Database
- Use Sequelize ORM
- MySQL as database
- Environment variables for credentials
